const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Does the AI write a full damp survey report?",
    answer: "The AI generates only the initial acknowledgement to the instructing party — confirming receipt, referencing the damp type and property details, and indicating that your survey and report will follow. Your moisture readings, diagnosis, remediation specification, costings, and PCA guarantee documentation are all prepared entirely by you based on your professional site assessment."
  },
  {
    question: "Will it respond to supplier and trade body emails?",
    answer: "The system learns during setup to differentiate genuine damp survey instructions from routine operational emails. DPC chemical supplier price lists, membrane manufacturer technical bulletins, PCA newsletter updates, and training course notifications are filtered out. Only genuine property survey and remediation enquiries trigger the automatic acknowledgement."
  },
  {
    question: "How does it handle homeowner contact-form submissions?",
    answer: "When a homeowner submits your contact form — 'we have damp patches in the bedroom and kitchen, the house is a 1930s semi, please can you come and have a look' — the AI sends a professional reply confirming your interest, asking which rooms are worst affected and when access suits them, and categorises the lead separately from solicitor instructions."
  },
  {
    question: "What does email response cost for damp proofing firms?",
    answer: `Priced at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as a channel add-on, email response ensures damp specialists never lose a solicitor instruction to a competitor who acknowledged faster. Pre-purchase damp surveys — typically £250 to £400 each — convert into remediation contracts worth £2,000 to £20,000 when the buyer proceeds with the purchase and commissions the recommended treatment.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I draft all subsequent correspondence personally?",
    answer: "Every communication after the initial acknowledgement is yours. Your survey appointment confirmation, the damp report itself, remediation specification, quotation, and any follow-up correspondence with the solicitor or homebuyer are composed and sent solely by you. The AI's involvement concludes with the receipt confirmation."
  },
  {
    question: "How is damp survey instruction data secured?",
    answer: "Solicitor instructions contain property addresses, purchase prices, mortgage conditions, surveyor findings, and buyer contact details — all commercially and legally sensitive. All email data is encrypted, stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR, and shared only with you. No instruction details are disclosed to competing damp firms or any third party."
